    <section id="perused-main" class="main-hero-grid">
        <div>
            <h1 class="portfolio-title">Perused</h1>
            <h3 class="portfolio-subtitle">— Publication Design, 2020 / Adobe InDesign, Illustrator, Photoshop
            </h3>

            <ul>
                <li>
                    <h4 class="portfolio-section">Objective —</h4>
                    <p class="portfolio-description">To create a magazine publication, masthead, covers for current and
                        upcoming issues, and pages for a table of contents, an opening spread, and additional spreads
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <h4 class="portfolio-section">About —</h4>
                    <p class="portfolio-description"><span>Perused</span> is a lifestyle magazine focused on publishing
                        informative
                        content on current trends that can be read with attention or skimmed through. Areas of focus
                        include arts and culture, crafts, travel, home and interiors, cooking, and more, with content
                        that is both national and international. The target audience is college students and young
                        adults who are interested in expanding their knowledge and trying out new lifestyle trends. </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <h4 class="portfolio-section">Process —</h4>
                    <p class="portfolio-description">A series of image making and typographic studies were practiced in
                        the creation of this publication. For this publication, special emphasis was placed on the scale
                        of images and the typographic experimentation as well as on having an organized layout. All
                        images in the magazine are from Unsplash and have been modified. Text is from three articles by
                        Terry Nguyen (Vox), June Xie (Delish), and Bettina Makalintal (Vice).
                    </p>
                </li>
            </ul>

        </div>
    </section>


